name: Bela Karolyi
summary: Bela Karolyi, the legendary gymnastics coach who guided Olympic champions Nadia Comaneci and Mary Lou Retton, passed away at 82. Karolyi's legacy is marked by his instrumental role in developing the USA Gymnastics program into a global powerhouse, leading to numerous Olympic gold medals. Despite his coaching success, Karolyi faced scrutiny after the Larry Nassar sexual abuse scandal, for which he was criticized for failing to protect gymnasts under his tutelage. Karolyi's passing has sparked mixed reactions, with some acknowledging his coaching achievements while others highlight the controversies that overshadowed his later years.
